# Stochastic Gradient Langevin Dynamics (SGLD) applied to Bayesian Logistic Regression (BLR)

This project contains Jupyter notebooks illustrating the application of the SGLD to Bayesian logistic regression.

The notebooks focus on the implementation and numerical evaluation of SGLD for posterior sampling and parameter estimation using real-world datasets. They provide reproducible examples of Bayesian inference based on this Langevin dynamics.

## Contents

- Implementation of a discrete version of SGLD
- Parameter estimation
- Two numerical experiments and visualization of results

## Mathematical Background

The theoretical analysis, convergence guarantees, and complexity results underlying the implementation are developed in:

### PhD Thesis

> Marelys Crespo Navas, *Stochastic algorithms for Bayesian estimation and Diffusion processes*, PhD Thesis, Université Toulouse III Paul Sabatier, 2024.

### Related Publication
> M. Crespo, S. Gadat and X. Gendre
> *Stochastic Gradient Langevin Dynamics for (weakly) log-concave posterior distributions*. Electron. J. Probab. 29 1 - 40, 2024.

